{"type":"compaction","id":"5d5c3127","parentId":"b7f5b812","timestamp":"2026-04-08T11:50:25.726Z","summary":"## Goal\nIteratively refine a Chinese-language article about Specification-Driven Development (SDD) based on user feedback, making it more accessible, well-structured, and analytically deep.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Use plain, conversational language — avoid academic jargon, English terms without explanation, or abstract expressions\n- Never use \"光谱\" (spectrum) — use alternatives like \"连续的区间\", \"权衡\", \"严谨度\"\n- All claims in practice/case sections must have verifiable source links; remove entries without clear citations\n- \"Constitution\" → translate as \"宪章\"\n- When analyzing tools/methods, structure as: commonality → differences → logic behind differences, supported by authoritative citations\n- User's personal observations should be integrated dialectically with other methodologies, not presented as the sole truth\n- Table formatting: don't use separate \"出处\" column; put citation numbers inline with source names (e.g., \"Amazon [5]\")\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Replaced \"规格光谱\" → \"规格严谨度\" throughout\n- [x] Removed 5 uncited entries from §2.5 (Google, Stripe, Netflix, Microsoft, Tesla), kept only Amazon [5], GitHub [15], AWS [18], 国内开发者社区 [29]\n- [x] Merged old §2.4 (国内工程实践) + §2.5 (大厂实践速览) into single §2.4\n- [x] Removed \"实践二：OpenSpec 工程化落地的深度踩坑\" and \"实践四：反对的声音\"\n- [x] Consolidated §2.4 into one table with inline citations, changed \"国内开发者\" to \"阿里云开发者社区\" / \"腾讯云开发者社区\"\n- [x] Swapped §2.3 and §2.4 order (cases first, then comparison)\n- [x] Completely rewrote §2.4 工具横向对比 with 3-part structure: commonality (通用SDD流水线) → 5 key differences (with Fowler [34], Spillwave [22], arXiv [23] citations) → logic behind differences\n- [x] Batch-simplified 32 instances of academic/jargon language across entire article\n- [x] Changed all \"Constitution\" to \"宪章\" (6 instances)\n- [x] Replaced \"编排 vs 委托的光谱\" → \"编排 vs 委托的权衡\", then later → \"管得多 vs 管得少\"\n- [x] Replaced remaining \"光谱\" → \"连续的区间\"\n- [x] Rewrote \"决定 SDD 实践效果的关键因素\" with 3-layer progressive structure (规格质量 → 知识库 → 全链路/组织视角), incorporating user's practice observations dialectically\n- [x] Restructured §3: 3.1 \"规格是什么：四个本质\" (3.1.1-3.1.4) + 3.2 \"决定 SDD 实践效果的关键因素\"\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Fix §5 issues: 5.4 \"SDD 作为 AI 编码的编译器\" feels abrupt — proposed changing to \"质量护栏\" direction\n- [ ] Merge §5.5 \"Vibe Coding 与 Spec-Driven 的张力\" and §5.6 \"规格的粒度悖论\" — they address the same underlying question (at what granularity to constrain AI)\n\n### Blocked\n- (none)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **知识库是SDD实践的关键**: User's practice insight that knowledge accumulation (编码规范/业务规则/接口声明/历史约束) matters more than tool choice, presented dialectically with arXiv [23] and ThoughtWorks [24] citations\n- **2.4 共性→差异→逻辑结构**: Deeper analysis replacing flat feature comparison table, with authoritative citations woven in\n- **3.1-3.4 合并为子章节**: Better structural balance with 3.2 as parallel section\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Confirm with user on §5.4 direction (\"质量护栏\" vs other framing)\n2. Confirm merge approach for §5.5 + §5.6\n3. Execute the §5 edits once user approves\n4. Review remaining sections (§4 \"没有银弹\", §5 rest) for similar issues\n5. Final full-article pass for any remaining jargon or \"光谱\" instances\n\n## Critical Context\n- Article file: `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-sdd-special/sdd-article.md`\n- Key citations used: [5] Amazon TLA+, [15] Spec Kit, [18] Kiro, [22] Spillwave analysis, [23] arXiv SDD survey, [24] ThoughtWorks Tech Radar, [28] OpenSpec+Superpowers integration, [29] 阿里云, [32] 腾讯云, [34] Martin Fowler SDD tools review\n- Fetched sources for reference: Martin Fowler's SDD tools article (martinfowler.com), Spillwave's GSD vs Spec Kit vs OpenSpec comparison (pub.spillwave.com), arXiv 2602.00180 SDD survey paper\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user requested two structural changes to the SDD article: merge section 5.4 into section 5.1, and merge sections 5.5 and 5.6 into a single section.\n\n## Early Progress\n- The assistant acknowledged both changes and began reading the file to locate the relevant sections.\n- The file was read starting from offset 395, revealing sections 4.4 through the beginning of section 5.3. The actual content of sections 5.4, 5.5, and 5.6 was in the truncated portion (after \"业务意图 → 规格\"的映射).\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The article is about SDD (Software Design Document) in the AI era, with section 5 covering \"AI 时代的 SDD：旧问题与新答案\".\n- Section 5.1 discusses how AI coding shifts the bottleneck from implementation to specification correctness.\n- Sections 5.2-5.3 cover the recursive validation problem and the risk of faithfully implementing wrong specs.\n- The truncated suffix likely contains the actual content of sections 5.4, 5.5, and 5.6 that need to be merged, plus the assistant's edits implementing the requested changes.","firstKeptEntryId":"2af1f607","tokensBefore":134097,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":false}
